    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-06-24</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-09-23T15:57:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Highways Bettering the Economy and Environment Act - Authorizes as an eligible project cost for the construction of a federal-aid highway the cost of improving habitat for pollinators (i.e. bees, birds, bats, and butterflies) on rights-of-way adjacent to such highways.</p> <p>Directs the Secretary of Transportation (DOT), in conjunction with the states, to carry out programs that encourage: (1) integrated vegetation management practices on roadsides and other transportation rights-of-ways, including reduced mowing; (2) the development of habitat for pollinators through planting of native forbs and grasses; and (3) research and demonstration projects on economic and environmental benefits and best practices for integrated vegetation management, reduced mowing, and planting of native forbs and grasses for pollinator habitat.</p> <p>Authorizes the use of federal funds for the provision of habitat for pollinators that is related to a federally-funded transportation project.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
